# Security

## Purpose

Prevent common vulnerabilities before auth/DB layers are added.

## When It Applies

Env files, API routes, user input handling, and dependency changes. See `docs/SECURITY.md`.

## Requirements

- Never commit `.env`, keys, or tokens.
- Server secrets stay server-side; only `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` in client.
- Validate all input with Zod via `parseRequest`.
- No raw SQL or string-concatenated queries (use adapters when DB arrives).
- Sanitize user-generated content before rendering (React escapes by default).
- Depend on `@repo/core/env` for typed env access.

## Examples

```typescript
// ✅ Validated input
const body = parseRequest(createUserSchema, await request.json());

// ✅ Server-only key
const apiKey = env.OPENAI_API_KEY; // server module only
```

## Bad Examples

```typescript
// ❌ Secret in client component
const key = process.env.OPENAI_API_KEY;

// ❌ Trusting client data without validation
const { email } = await request.json();

// ❌ Logging full request bodies with passwords
logger.info('login', { body: req.body });
```
